From: Biju Sreedharan Nair <biju@sykatiya.com>
Sent: Wednesday, April 30, 2025 8:47 PM
To: Midhun Abraham <midhun.a@sykatiya.com>
Cc: Srinivas Rao Bethanamudi <bsrao@sykatiya.com>
Subject: Re: Evaluation Board details.

Hi Mithun,

I see that the Microchip ATSAM has 2 MB of SDRAM and the description says t=
hat it is good for full UDS stack development. Eventhough S32K is equally g=
ood, the size of SRAM in S32K is relatively less.
Can you please check the supported compiler tool chains that is being suppo=
rted by Microchip ? We may not be able to use Keil or IAR. Please see wheth=
er it has support for GCC.

Regards, Biju
